Deckers Outdoor Corp. (DECK) , maker of the
Uggs boot brand, gained after Chief Executive Officer Angel
Martinez bought 10,000 shares.  The shares rose 1.2 percent to $46.98 at the close in  New
York . The Goleta, California-based companyâ€™s stock has declined
38 percent this year.  Martinez, who became CEO in 2005, purchased the shares
starting on July 11, according to a filing with the U.S.
Securities and Exchange Commission. He now owns 346,740 shares,
or about 0.9 percent of the company.  To contact the reporter on this story:
